{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2016}} {{Infobox document | document_name = Constitution of the Year XII | image = Constitution de l'an XII. Page 1 - Archives Nationales - AE-II-1512.jpg | image_size = | image_alt = | caption = Constitution of the Year XII (1804). | orig_lang_code = fr | title_orig = {{fr}} Constitution de l'an XII | date_created = | date_presented = | date_ratified = 1804 | date_effective = | date_repeal = 1814 | location_of_document = | commissioned = | writer = | signers = | media_type = | subject = | purpose = }}
The '''Constitution of the Year XII''' was a national [[constitution]] of [[France]] adopted during the Year XII of the [[French Revolutionary Calendar]] (1804 in the [[Gregorian calendar]]).
It amended the earlier [[Constitution of the Year VIII]] and [[Constitution of the Year X]], establishing the [[First French Empire]] with [[Napoleon I of France|Napoleon Bonaparte]] &mdash; previously [[French Consulate|First Consul]] for Life, with wide-ranging powers &mdash; as Napoleon I, [[Emperor of the French]]. The Constitution established the [[House of Bonaparte]] as France's imperial dynasty, making the throne hereditary in Napoleon's family. The Constitution of the Year XII was later itself extensively amended by the [[Charter of 1815|Additional Act]] and definitively abolished with the final return of the [[House of Bourbon|Bourbons]] in 1815.
==See also== *[[French constitutional referendum, 1804]]
