{{Infobox prepared food | name = Fritule | image = Fritule(miske).JPG | image_size = 250px | caption = | country = [[Croatia]] | region = | creator = | course = | type = [[Doughnut]] | served = | main_ingredient = [[Batter (cooking)|batter]], [[rum]], [[citrus zest]], [[raisin]]s, [[powdered sugar]] | variations = | calories = | other = }}
'''Fritule''' is a festive [[Croatia]]n pastry made particularly for Christmas. They resemble little [[doughnut]]s, the Italian [[zeppole]], Venetian [[frìtole]], and the Dutch Christmas snack "[[oliebollen]]" ("balls of oil"). However, they are usually flavored with rum and citrus zest, containing [[raisin]]s, and are topped with [[powdered sugar]].
