e Maru|SS ''Kiche Maru'']] |22 September 1912 |A Japanese passenger ship that sank in a storm with over 1,000 passengers lost. | |- |''[[Kitagawa Maru No.5]]'' |April 1957 |A Japanese wooden passenger boat that capsized off [[Onomichi]], [[Seto Inland Sea|Inland Sea]], killing at least 113. | |- |[[Russian battleship Knyaz Suvorov|''Knyaz Suvorov'']] |27 May 1905 |A Russian battleship that was sunk at the [[Battle of Tsushima]]. | |- |''[[Lisbon Maru]]'' |2 October 1942 |A [[troopship]] and prisoner-of-war transport that was torpedoed by [[USS Grouper (SS-214)|USS ''Grouper'']] off [[Zhoushan]]. |{{coord|30.23|N|122.765|E|name=Lisbon Maru}} |- |[[Japanese cruiser Nagara|''Nagara'']] |7 August 1944 |A [[Nagara-class cruiser|''Nagara''-class]] [[light cruiser]] that was torpedoed by [[USS Croaker (SS-246)|USS ''Croaker'']] off [[Amakusa]]. |{{coord|32|09|N|129|53|E|name=Japanese cruiser Nagara}} |- |''Nankai Maru'' |January 1958 |A ferry between [[Wakayama, Wakayama|Wakayama]] and [[Tokushima, Tokushima|Tokushima]] that capsized off southern [[Awaji Island]], killing at least 167. | |- |[[Japanese cruiser Nisshin|''Nisshin'']] |18 January 1942 |A [[Kasuga-class cruiser|''Kasuga''-class]] [[armored cruiser]] that was sunk as a target southwest of [[Kure, Hiroshima|Kure]]. |{{coord|34|05|N|132|53|E|name=Japanese cruiser Nisshin}} |- |[[Nossa Senhora da Graça incident|''Nossa Senhora da Graça'']] |6 January 1610 |A Portuguese [[carrack]] that was sunk by its own captain in the mouth of [[Nagasaki Bay]] after being boarded by Japanese samurai and set on fire. | |- |[[Japanese destroyer Numakaze|''Numakaze'']] |18 December 1943 |A [[Minekaze-class destroyer|''Minekaze''-class]] [[destroyer]] that was sunk northeast of [[Naha, Okinawa|Naha]]. |{{coord|26|29|N|128|26|E|name=Japanese destroyer Numakaze}} |- |[[Japanese destroyer Okikaze|''Okikaze'']] |10 January 1943 |A [[Minekaze-class destroyer|''Minekaze''-class]] [[destroyer]] that was torpedoed by [[USS Trigger (SS-237)|