or|''Thor'']] |30 November 1942 |An [[auxiliary cruiser]] that was destroyed by fire while moored at [[Yokohama]], and abandoned. |{{coord|35|23|50|N|139|38|50|E|name=German auxiliary cruiser Thor}} |- |[[USS Thornton (DD-270)|USS ''Thornton'']] |2 May 1945 |A [[Clemson-class destroyer|''Clemson''-class]] [[destroyer]] that was beached in the [[Ryukyu Islands]] after taking damage in a collision. | |- |''[[Tofuku Maru]]'' |24 December 1943 |A [[hell ship]] that was torpedoed by [[USS Gurnard (SS-254)|USS ''Gurnard'']] off the east coast of [[Honshu]]. |{{coord|34|02|N|136|19|E|name=Tofuku Maru}} |- |''[[Tokiwa Maru]]'' | |A regular route ferry between [[Naruto]] and [[Kobe]]. It capsized in a collision with the cargo ship ''Richmond Maru'' off Kobe, with at least 47 confirmed dead. | |- |[[Japanese battleship Tosa|''Tosa'']] |9 February 1925 |A [[Tosa-class battleship|''Tosa''-class]] [[battleship]] that was scuttled south of [[Mizunokojima Lighthouse]]. | |- |''[[Tōya Maru]]'' |26 September 1954 |A [[train ferry]] that sank in a typhoon off [[Hakodate, Hokkaidō|Hakodate]], resulting in around 1,153 deaths. |{{coord|41.1932|N|140.152|E|name=Tōya Maru}} |- |''Toyo Maru No 10'' |November 1945 |A passenger ferry sank by overloaded three times capacity, off Hakata Island, [[Seto Inland Sea]], at least 397 person confirmed dead. |<ref>[[:ja:第十東予丸沈没事故]] '''(Japanese languag)''' Retrieved date February 12, 2016.</ref> |- |''[[Tsushima Maru]]'' |22 August 1944 |A passenger ship that was sunk by [[USS Bowfin (SS-287)|USS ''Bowfin'']] off [[Akusekijima]], killing 1,484 civilians, including 767 schoolchildren. |{{coord|29|32|33|N|129|33|30|E|name=Tsushima Maru}} |- |[[Russian armoured cruiser Vladimir Monomakh|''Vladimir Monomakh'']] |28 May 1905 |An [[armored cruiser]] that was damaged by Japanese torpedo boats and scuttled off [[Tsushima Island]]. |{{coord|34|32|N|129|40|E|name=Russian armored cruiser Vladimir Monomakh}} |}
