aughter after it was revealed the ship was heavily overbalanced, and that the captain and crew abandoned ship after ordering the passengers to remain seated even as water began filling the ship, resulting in unnecessary deaths. | {{Coord|34|13|5|N|125|57|0|E|type:event_dim:10km|name=Sewol}} |- |''Yeong-ho'' |October 1963 |A Yeonhwa Island to Mokpo route ferry, capsized off [[Jeollanam-do]]. According to South Korean Coast Guard official confirmed report, 140 person lost to lives, only a person rescued. |<ref>[[:ko:연호 침몰 사고]] '''(Korean language)''' Retrieved 2017-02-17.</ref> |}
