{{More citations needed|date=May 2008}}
{{Infobox musical artist <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject_Musicians --> | name = Ronin | image = | caption = | image_size = | background = group_or_band | alias = | origin = [[Singapore]] | genre = [[Rock music|Rock]] | years_active = 2003–present | label = [[Universal Music Group|Universal]] | associated_acts = | website = http://myspace.com/ronin | current_members = Sean Cheng, Derryn Wong, Simon Lee, Bang Ong | past_members = Levan Wee }}
'''Ronin''' is a [[Rock music|rock]] band based in [[Singapore]]. They are infamous{{Citation needed|date=August 2014}} for their live performances and being one of the few high-profile rock bands around. Before their entry to the mainstream market, the band launched a [[Self-publishing|self-released]] [[Extended play|EP]] which included 5 songs, and later released an [[LP album|LP]] which was hugely successful{{Citation needed|date=August 2014}}<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://juice.com.sg/leonard-soosays-10-greatest-anthems-singapore/|title=Leonard Soosay's 10 greatest anthems for Singapore {{!}} JUICE Singapore|date=2017-08-09|work=JUICE Singapore|access-date=2018-10-31|language=en-GB}}</ref>. Their debut album ''Do or Die'' has received rave reviews{{Citation needed|date=August 2014}} by local press, and is one of the top selling English-language albums in Singapore of all time{{Citation needed|date=August 2014}}. In 2006, the band collaborated with local [[Mediacorp]] artiste [[Fiona Xie]] in a love song duet, entitled "Love Will Shine on Through". The song was recorded to raise funds for a [[cancer]] project, with a [[book]] and a [[CD]] recorded together. One of their songs, "One More Moment", was covered by Singaporean artiste [[Ho Yeow Sun]].
The band enjoyed a number one hit called ''Black Maria'' in the Singapore charts, the song ''Crazy Son'' reached third.<ref name="cdbaby">[http://cdbaby.com/cd/ronintunes CD Baby] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080621125254/http://cdbaby.com/cd/ronintunes |date=2008-06-21 }} - notes on "Do or Die"</ref> Ronin has also written the theme song and title soundtrack 'Memories' for the film ''[[Singapore Dreaming]]''.<ref>[http://www.funkygrad.com/lifestyle/displayarticle.php?artID=808&subcat=popcorn www.funkygrad.com] {{webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20130123214204/http://www.funkygrad.com/lifestyle/displayarticle.php?artID=808&subcat=popcorn |date=2013-01-23 }} - Ronin interview</ref><ref>[http://www.singaporedreaming.com/fullcredits.htm www.singaporedreaming.com] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080204140607/http://www.singaporedreaming.com/fullcredits.htm |date=2008-02-04 }} – Full credits</ref>
On 24 June 2007, lead singer Levan Wee performed with the band for the last time, due to a combination of personal issues, as well as differences in musical direction<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.soft.com.sg/forum/showthread.php?29640-Levan-left-Ronin|title=Levan left Ronin|website=www.soft.com.sg|language=en|access-date=2018-10-31}}</ref>. He is now the lead singer of ASTRONINJA. The band has since returned to the studios to continue work on their 2nd LP.{{Update after|2014|8|19}}
==Members==
===Current members===
* Sean Cheng: [[Singing|Vocals]], [[Guitars]] * Simon Lee: [[Guitar]] * Derryn Wong: [[Bass guitar|Bass]] * Bang Ong: [[Drum kit|Drums]]
All 4 members of Ronin were students from [[Victoria School]]. The band members have cameo appearances in the movie "Anna & Anna", starring Golden Horse winner Karena Lam. They appear as the backing band of the film's lead actor, Tender Huang.
===Previous members===
* Levan Wee: [[Singing|Vocals]] (Left in 2007)
==Discography== * ''The EP'' - a 5-song EP which was self-released on January 2004. It was recorded at Snakeweed Studios, produced by Leonard Soosay and Ronin, and mastered at 301 Studios in Sydney. * ''Do or Die'' - a full-length album released on August 2005 and distributed by [[Universal Music Group|Universal Music]].<ref name="cdbaby"/> Recorded at Snakeweed Studios and produced by Leonard Soosay and Ronin.
