{{Orphan|date=September 2017}}

{{italicstitle}}
'''''The Cape Chronicle''''' was a newspaper that operated from [[Cape Town]] in the [[Cape Colony]], for a brief period from 1870 to 1871. It was edited by William Foster, who had previously edited the ''[[Cape Standard]]'' in the 1860s.<ref>K.Vernon: ''Penpricks: The Drawing of South Africa's Political Battlelines''. New Africa Books, 2000. p.19.</ref>

