[[File:Angsbacka association.jpg|thumb|right|Ängsbacka Association meeting]]
{{Primary sources|section|date=August 2018}}

'''Ängsbacka''' is a course and festival center focused on personal development, spirituality and self-expression. It is located in [[Molkom]], Sweden, and was started in 1996.<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.mynewsdesk.com/se/pressreleases/aengsbacka-kursgaard-fyller-20-aar-1295487 |title=Ängsbacka kursgård fyller 20 år! - Ängsbacka Kursgård |website=Mynewsdesk.com |date=2016-02-03 |accessdate=2017-04-25}}</ref>

The center hosts an average of seven festivals per year,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.angsbacka.se/festivals/ |title=Festivals - Ängsbacka Community |website=En.angsbacka.se |date=2014-06-20 |accessdate=2017-04-25}}</ref> mainly during the summer. The [[No Mind Festival]] is the largest of them with around a thousand participants.

It is registered as a not-for-profit organization<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.angsbacka.se/about-angsbacka/angsbacka-association/ |title=Ängsbacka Association - Ängsbacka Community |website=En.angsbacka.se |date=2014-06-20 |accessdate=2017-04-25}}</ref> owned by members and is run in a large part by volunteers.

The course center and its No Mind Festival were the feature of the 2008 documentary ''[[Three Miles North of Molkom]]''.

